 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Dynamic time warping\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example, we use dynamic time warping (DTW) and Weighted DTW."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pylab as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib.collections import LineCollection\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "from wildboar.distance.dtw import (\n",
    "    dtw_alignment,\n",
    "    wdtw_alignment,\n",
    "    dtw_mapping,\n",
    "    dtw_distance,\n",
    "\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load a dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data, _ = load_dataset(\"Wafer\")\n",
    "x = data[0]\n",
    "y = data[1]\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we define a function that we use to plot the alignment between two time series under DTW."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_alignment(x, y, idx):\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "    ax.plot(x)\n",
    "    ax.plot(y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    lines = [[(a, x[a]), (b, y[b])] for a, b in zip(*idx)]\n",
    "    collection = LineCollection(lines, color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "    ax.add_collection(collection)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Dynamic Time Warping\n",
    "\n",
    "In the first exampe, we use traditional dynamic time warping and a band of size 7."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_alignment(x, y, dtw_mapping(alignment=dtw_alignment(x, y, r=0.05)).nonzero())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Weighted Dynamic Time Warping\n",
    "\n",
    "In the second example, we plot the alignment path under weighted DTW with the penelty parameter set to 0.5."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_alignment(x, y, dtw_mapping(alignment=wdtw_alignment(x, y, g=0.05)).nonzero())"
   ]
  }
 ],
